                            <comment id="12575505" author="allee8285" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2008 21:58:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Configurations.runAgainstAllAnchors() method, all the persistence units (anchors) from the configuration paths are first identified and  each anchor is then processed by the tool&apos;s runnable class. If no persistence unit is found, this method just returns back to the tool&apos;s main().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For schema and possibly other supported tools, persistence unit is not a required parameter. E.g. schema&apos;s -reflect action.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a patch of the Configurations class allowing the parent tool to process the original tool semantics if no persistence unit (anchor) is found. In the case of SchemaTool, it will perform the desire function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comments and suggestions are appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Albert Lee.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
